<TEXT>
air force gen samuel 
phillips who headed nasas apollo program when the united states 
put the first man on the moon died wednesday of heart failure he 
was 68 
phillips who retired as a fourstar air force general in 1975 
headed the apollo lunar landing program of the national aeronautics 
and space administration from 1964 to 1969 
he returned to nasa in 1986 to conduct a management review and 
recommend changes in the wake of the challenger disaster 
phillips long and distinguished air force career included tours 
as director of the minuteman intercontinental ballistic missile 
program from 19591963 vice commander of the ballistic systems 
division at norton air force base san bernardino from 19631964 
and commander of air force systems command at andrews afb 
maryland from 1973 to 1975 
after retiring from the air force phillips joined trw in el 
segundo as general manager of its energy systems management 
division in 1984 he became vice president of trws defense 
systems group he retired from trw in 1986 but continued to serve 
in an advisory capacity 
phillips is survived by his wife betty anne and three 
daughters dana mcmenamin of sacramento janie phillips of el 
segundo and kathleen esposito of redondo beach 
</TEXT>
