<TEXT>
an institute devoted solely to aids research 
will open this year in manhattan launched with 114 million in 
foundation and city funds and is expected to grow into one of the 
worlds largest aids laboratories 
dr david ho 37 an aids researcher and member of the aids 
advisory committee of the us centers for disease control will be 
director of the new aaron diamond aids research center 
the center will concentrate on creating an aids vaccine and 
preventing the damage aids causes to people already infected 
officials said 
when a cure for aids is found it will be in a place such as 
this mayor david n dinkins said at a news conference 
the sponsors said the center would rank in size with such 
leading aids programs as the pasteur institute and the national 
institutes of health in bethesda md in about two years 
the center started with 3 million from the diamond foundation 
and 34 million in city construction and renovation funds is 
expected to open in about six months and will be housed rentfree 
in the citys department of health laboratories building 
the diamond foundation also has promised 1 million a year 
toward the centers operating budget for the first five years 
its immediate goal is to attract about 50 topnotch scientists 
many of whom already have federal research grants and gather them 
under one roof for collaboration said ho who was lured from the 
university of california at los angeles 
ho predicted it will take several years for researchers at the 
center or elsewhere to develop a successful aids vaccine and 
several more years to put it into widespread use 
the diamond foundation was established by the late real estate 
developer aaron diamond who died in 1984 it finances medical 
research minority education arts and human rights programs 
</TEXT>
