<TEXT>
the bush adminstrations refusal to deal with libya 
is complicating an international campaign to rid africa of a deadly 
pest that threatens livestock wildlife and even humans 
the parasitic screwworm fly is proving to be a political 
insect said a source at the un food and agriculture 
organization the united states has the expertise and libya has 
the pest 
so far washington has agreed to allow critically needed us 
technology to be used in libya to combat the insect but us 
sanctions against libya mean the technology cant be quickly 
authorized and crucial months have passed 
also the united states has refused a request by the un 
organization to allow americans with vitally needed experience go 
to libya to help eradicate the insect 
we would have been able to have the fullscale eradication 
campaign under way if it werent for the obstacles from the us 
side said the fao source who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the screwworm fly lodges in wounds or tick bites and can kill 
its hosts including humans by eating away at tissues in addition 
to livestock wildlife such as zebras and antelopes as well as some 
endangered species are threatened 
a small but undetermined number of people in libya have been 
infested with the parasite 
time is crucial to containing the fly which until its 
appearance in libya had not been seen outside the western 
hemisphere 
