the united states will absolve 10 african 
countries of about 305 million in debt the us agency for 
international development announced today 
the countries are pursuing economic reform programs approved by 
the international monetary fund or the world bank 
they are benin cameroon ghana guinea kenya madagascar 
malawi mali nigeria and zaire 
in some cases there will be further relief extended in stages 
an aid statement said three other countries eligible for relief 
ivory coast niger and uganda have not concluded agreements with 
the united states 
together they would boost the forgiven debt relief to 745 
million 
subsaharan african countries owe the us government 65 
billion including 15 billion for economic assistance loans 
