a school bus whose driver momentarily took 
his eyes off the road to look through the rearview mirror plowed 
into two trees injuring the driver and all but two of the 38 
children aboard authorities said today 
eighteen of the children were hospitalized after tuesdays 
accident six in critical or serious condition with head injuries 
officials said 
the bus carrying kindergarteners and firstgraders from the 
harriman heights road elementary school sheared off its roof in 
the accident 
state trooper robert gillespie said the bus slipped into the 
muddy shoulder apparently after the driver took his eyes off the 
road for a moment 
the driver andrew callahan 63 was listed in fair condition 
with head injuries today 
gillespie said state police would consult with the district 
attorney today on whether to bring charges against callahan 
callahan is a 23year veteran of the districts routes and had 
never had an accident said cliff berchtold monroewoodbury 
district transportation director 
i was going home and the bus went into the ditch and i hit the 
seat with my head a couple of times said martin polignone 6 
who had a bump on his head and a bruise under his eye 
i fell into the mud head first said 6yearold kristin 
aspinwall he the driver moved over and the wheel got off the 
road and the bus tipped over and the whole roof came off 
the bus which lacked passenger seat belts was built a year 
before state law required them in 1986 
the school was closed today and louis ciota assistant 
