<TEXT>
the government today accused pakistan of 
encouraging terrorism and subversion in kashmir where indian 
security forces are trying to put down a moslem rebellion 
pakistans foreign minister sahabzada yaqub khan on tuesday 
accused india of trying to supress the freedom movement in 
kashmir through atrocities khans speech was broadcast by 
national radio and television 
an indian foreign ministry spokesman aftab seth said khans 
statements were deliberately fallacious and amounted to 
direct incitement to subversion violence and terrorist activties 
in a part of india 
the indian government faces a violent islamic separatist 
movement in kashmir that has grown more strident in the past two 
months in an effort to end the rebellion indian troops and police 
launched a crackdown jan 20 
at least 72 people most of them moslem protesters shot by 
indian security forces were killed in kashmir between jan 20 and 
jan 25 according to figures compiled from government spokesmen 
police sources and witnesses the government says there have been 
no deaths since jan 25 
khan had claimed in his speech that thousands of kashmiris were 
being detained and hundreds have died in the crackdown 
india has often accused pakistan of aiding the militants in 
order to annex the kashmir valley a predominantly moslem region 
sandwiched between northwestern india and northeastern pakistan 
india and pakistan fought wars in 1965 and 1971 over border 
disputes in the region 
pakistan denies helping the militants but says it supports 
kashmiri separatism calling it a movement for selfdetermination 
seth said khans speech indicated that his government persists 
in its efforts to involve itself in our internal affairs we would 
like to firmly reiterate that kashmir is and will continue to be an 
integral part of india 
a portion of kashmir has been under dispute since 1947 when 
india and pakistan were partitioned on gaining independence from 
britain india controls most of the mountainous region and 
pakistan occupies a smaller sector 
seth said the only issue that remains to be resolved in 
kashmir is the vacation by pakistan of territory illegally occupied 
by it he said khans efforts to justify pakistani policies will 
fuel tension in kashmir 
kashmiri separatists who earlier demanded union of kashmir with 
pakistan now demand independence and the formation of a neutral 
country 
