<TEXT>
up to 5 feet of snow blanketed parts 
of south korea on wednesday paralyzing traffic in the capital and 
isolating villages 
no weatherrelated deaths had been reported as of late wednesday 
but weathermen posted severe snow warnings for the entire nation 
they forecast 4 to 8 inches of new snow by thursday 
kimpo international airport outside seoul stayed open but six 
domestic airports along the east and southern coasts were closed 
all outbound intercity buses from seoul were canceled 
thousands of boats were forced to take shelter in port beause of 
high waves churned by galeforce winds maritime police said 
more than 98 inches of snow accumulated in seoul by wednesday 
snarling traffic on icy streets 
the east coast was hit hardest with 5 feet of snow that cut off 
mountain roads collapsed dozens of slate roofs 
in seoul subways were overcrowded and vehicular traffic moved 
at a snails pace all government workers were asked to report to 
work an hour late to try to reduce congestion about 3000 city 
employees were mobilized to control traffic and clear streets of 
snow 
</TEXT>
