as thousands enjoyed their first big macs from 
moscows new mcdonalds dozens of others stood at tiny tables in a 
dim dingy cafeteria a few blocks away wednesday and ate the 
standard fare of meat and potatoes 
but for all its problems the popular zelyeny ogonyok a snack 
bar on pushkin street does have a few things mcdonalds doesnt 
low prices experienced workers and a solid reputation 
this is a good place i come here whenever i can said 
alexei a middleaged construction workers who sipped cabbage soup 
he admitted hed rather be at mcdonalds which opened for 
business wednesday on pushkin square 
zelyeny ogonyok russian for green light in keeping with its 
predominant clientele of taxi drivers is reputed to be one of 
moscows best snack shops with good food and service it even has 
its own golden arches of sorts cylindrical signs outside painted 
gold and green 
but the decor and ambiance leave something to be desired 
theres no place to hang a coat or hat so diners must wear them 
theres no place to sit so they must stand the small chandeliers 
are so weak customers can barely see what theyre eating which 
may be a good thing 
a popular main dish wednesday was a large meatball served cold 
with beads of fat inside the price just 28 kopecks or about 10 
minutes pay for an average worker compared to 375 rubles for a 
big mac more than two hours pay the most expensive item on the 
menu was a meat stew priced at 43 kopecks or 15 minutes work 
the cheapest was a piece of russian black bread for 1 kopeck 
elderly women in white smocks and caps scurried around clearing 
tables and serving food behind a counter 
there were few smiles or greetings that are musts for mcdonalds 
employees but customers with good eyesight could make out 
spasibo russian or thank you on each cash register receipt 
alexei and several workers of zelyeny ogonyok said they had 
heard reports about the new mcdonalds which has gotten a big dose 
of free publicity on staterun tv and in such publications as 
pravda izvestia and moscow news 
were waiting for them to invite our entire work collective 
120 people joked alexandra s bobrova the director of zelyeny 
ogonyok 
