<TEXT>
a panel of experts is recommending that the 
antiaids drug azt be prescribed more widely for people in early 
stages of infection by the virus that causes aids 
research has clearly established that azt or zidovudine 
delays the onset of aids in people infected with the human 
immunodeficiency virus or hiv the food and drug administration 
advisory committee said tuesday 
but the committee also emphasized the need to carefully study 
and document the potential risks associated with prolonged 
zidovudine therapy especially those related to the drugs 
cancercausing potential and any possible unique effects on 
womens fetuses and children 
azt is approved for use in patients who have fullblown aids 
but a governmentsponsored study has shown the drug can prolong the 
lives of people in earlier stages of the disease 
some physicians already prescribe the drug for people with early 
or no symptoms of aids 
last august officials at the national institute of allergy and 
infectious diseases announced that clinical trials showed azt 
significantly slows progression of aids in patients with early 
symptoms and no symptoms the results were so promising that of 
officials stopped the clinical trial and began offering azt to all 
patients in the study including those who had been receiving 
placebos for comparison 
the antiviral drugs advisory committee unanimously agreed the 
fda should recommend use of azt in people with levels of critical 
immune system cells called t4 cells under 500 per cubic 
millimeter 
the drug is now recommended for use in people whose t4 cells 
are below 200 disease in such patients is considered to be in an 
advanced stage and many such patients have fullblown aids 
azt made by burroughs wellcome co is the only fdaapproved 
drug that combats the aids virus directly it is being used by more 
than 40000 people in the united states 
as many as 500000 of the estimated 800000 to 13 million 
people in the united states infected with hiv the virus that 
causes aids are believed to have t4 cell counts between 200 and 
500 according to the public health service however many of these 
people do not know they are infected with hiv 
