although he cautioned that east germans should not decide this 
important issue on the streets 
weekly prodemocracy rallies in leipzig and other major cities 
have taken on a clear proreunification atmosphere recently 
west german newspapers reported gorbachevs comments prominently 
and hailed his apparent acceptance of german reunification as 
coming to grips with reality 
gorbachev has once again shown himself to be a politician of 
realism who has correctly analyzed the developments in east germany 
and the will of the people genscher told west german radio 
klein quoted kohl as telling his cabinet that gorbachevs 
tentative approval of eventual reunification could give east 
germans hope of better days to come and halt the exodus 
we want all people in east germany to find their opportunities 
in life in their own land kohl said according to klein 
resettlement must be left as a last resort jobs and homes are in 
limited supply in west germany 
the west german constitution recognizes all ethnic germans as 
citizens and provides them with generous resettlement aid when they 
immigrate 
but the influx of more than 340000 east germans last year and 
an exit trend that threatens to drive a million more to the west 
this year has heightened social tensions in west germany 
kohl suggested gorbachev had eased the fears of east germans by 
making clear that the kremlin would not stand in the way of 
reunification 
