<TEXT>
many susitna valley moose calves weakened 
by this winters heavy snow are starving to death in yards and 
driveways and some people are feeding the animals despite caution 
from wildlife biologists 
ive got a couple moose in front of my house right now and 
the mama looks ok but the baby is sure looking poorly it looks 
sick its frosted all over said resident david spain 
spain said a moose calf walked into the shop where he works as a 
mechanic and died after hanging around outside for four weeks 
snow is nearly 5 feet deep at willow in the valley 55 miles 
north of anchorage the national weather service says 
moose numbers normally decline during severe winters because 
young weak animals must struggle harder to find food and move 
through the snow 
but the susitna valley has not had a winter this bad in years 
and the moose population was especially high when this years heavy 
snow began 
the snow has also led to more moose deaths on highways police 
logs have shown up to 22 moose accidentally killed in a single 
night there is no count of how many calves have died of starvation 
were so swamped with calls that if we get somebodys name and 
get them down in our notebooks were lucky said fish and 
wildlife protection trooper sgt richard graham 
bill collins a fish and game wildlife biologist said his 
palmer office receives a dozen calls a day from residents who want 
to know what to do about hungry moose 
once the moose are fed they are extremely reluctant to leave 
that area collins said when conditions improve theyll still 
stay around 
if the feeding area is near where people live the moose can be 
dangerous collins said 
the more a wild animal becomes accustomed to human beings the 
more likely it is to bridge the gap between standing off and 
staying away or thrashing someone collins said 
he said a moose that had been fed tried to push its way into a 
womans house recently in another case last week a calf tried to 
get into a house then trampled a woman when she got out of her 
car collins said the 300pound calf threatened to attack him too 
and he had to kill it 
ive been hit and kicked down a couple of times already this 
year graham said 
if a calf cannot move graham shoots it he said because 
otherwise it will only suffer and die slowly 
