responsibility for everything boomerangs to the very top said 
the article signed by managing editor alexander drozdov 
we cannot we do not have the right to risk gorbachev simply 
because he inherited such a heavy ideological and personnel 
burden he continued referring to hardline holdovers from the 
communist partys decades of dictatorship 
today only he is in a position to become the center of gravity 
and a mediator between the many political and social forces 
drozdov wrote 
drozdov also said in his frontpage article that it is high 
time for all influential participants in the political process to 
sit down at a roundtable in obvious reference to negotiations 
in poland in which communists agreed to loosen their control over 
the country the talks led to the election of the soviet blocs 
first noncommunist prime minister 
