<TEXT>
the house on wednesday brushed aside efforts 
to delay a bill to ease voter registration procedures as what 
lawmakers had once billed as bipartisan harmony dissolved into 
partyline bickering 
the house on a key procedural vote upheld 254166 a rule 
requiring critics to tie all of their proposed amendments to the 
legislation into a single bundle 
the house will then hold just one vote on the whole package next 
week when it turns to the legislation itself 
and so begins the great voter registration debate of 1990 
said rep lynn martin rill except that it wont be that great 
a debate 
the socalled motor voter bill would make voter registration 
automatic for any eligible american applying for a drivers 
license other provisions would allow registration by postcard and 
at various government offices 
critics spurred on the bush administration object to the rule 
giving them just one floor vote on all proposed amendments 
led by house minority leader robert h michel rill they want 
to junk restrictions on the offering of floor amendments such an 
open rule would give individual amendments a better chance of 
being adopted and also slow down house action on the bill 
on monday the minority leader swooped into town and trashed 
the entire agreement declared rep al swift dwash a chief 
sponsor of the bill 
