the three largest political parties 
agreed wednesday in an apparent effort at national unity that the 
next president should have a coalition cabinet 
the agreement among the liberal conservative and patriotic 
union parties will apply to the person who is elected may 27 and 
takes office aug 7 
president virgilio barco a liberal has earned international 
praise for his war on drug traffickers but squabbling among the 
three parties has cost him support at home 
colombias constitution limits a president to one term of four 
years 
