the deed and unfortunately both are dead wrong 
capital gains are profits from the sale of stock and other 
investments since a lower tax rate for capital gains was repealed 
in 1986 rostenkowski noted the value of stocks on the new york 
stock exchange has risen 40 percent 
i am not claiming that our tax laws have boosted the market 
rostenkowski said to the contrary i am arguing that the market 
has a dynamic of its own that is generally independent of our tax 
laws 
the chairman also expressed his distaste for special tax breaks 
offered as incentives to encourage saving ive become convinced 
that most tax incentives simply dont work he said and 
the few that do work dont work very well 
bush is asking congress to create a new savings plan that would 
allow a couple with income of 120000 or less to avoid tax on 
interest earned on special accounts held at least seven years 
