mainstream militia backed by syria 
the fighting in the christian zone was the worst since february 
1989 when aouns troops last moved against the lebanese forces 
the main christian militia led by samir geagea more than 80 people 
were killed and 200 wounded in that fourday conflict 
aouns gunners in the hills east of beirut hammered geageas 
seafront headquarters in the karantina district with heavy 155mm 
howitzer barrages 
geageas fighters hit back with salvos of rockets from launchers 
that spat 40 missiles a minute on the shellwrecked presidential 
palace in suburban baabda where aoun has his headquarters 
police said both leaders were reported to be unharmed 
exploding shells and rockets streaked over the burning christian 
sector of the city and lighted up the night sky 
a police statement said at least 28 people were killed and 69 
wounded from fierce daylong battles with tanks and artillery in the 
christian sector and north lebanon 
this is an initial count the toll is definitely much higher 
as scores of other casualties were still bleeding in embattled 
areas that ambulances and rescuers could not reach the statement 
said 
at least seven civilians including a 6monthold baby were 
killed and 16 wounded by stray shells that exploded in west and 
