president bush preparing to deliver his first 
state of the union address telephoned soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev on wednesday to propose deeper cuts in us and soviet 
combat troops in europe officials said 
bush was to announce the plan formally in a nationally broadcast 
appearance before a joint session of congress the proposal to 
reduce forces of each country to 195000 in the affected area was 
described by senior administration officials as a response to the 
rapidly falling deck of cards in eastern europe amid the 
collapse of hardline communist regimes 
the proposal won immediate praise from democrats including sen 
sam nunn chairman of the armed services committee who said it fit 
the changing circumstances in europe and the fiscal pressures at 
home 
