president bush acclaiming the revolution of 
89 in eastern europe proposed a sharp new cut in us and 
soviet combat forces wednesday night and told a joint meeting of 
congress that the time is right to move forward in europe 
in his first state of the union address bush also announced 
plans to withdraw well before the end of february the last 
3000 troops from a force of 14000 sent to panama to oust gen 
manuel antonio noriega 
democrats and republicans alike assembled in joint session of 
congress to hear the president stood in ovation when bush said 
one year ago the people of panama lived in fear under the thumb 
