capt arthur hastings philip jackson as inspector japp and 
pauline moran as poirots secretary miss lemon the setting is 
1935 so the stories reflect the fashions atmosphere and politics 
of britains upper class in places ranging from england to the 
mediterranean 
poirot is of course noted for his little gray cells and 
his uncanny ability to unmask all the killers kidnappers 
poisoners plotters thieves and treacherous lovers who cross his 
path 
hes eccentric eating a breakfast every day of two boiled eggs 
that must be exactly the same size and compulsively tidying up any 
room he walks into 
hes very smart hes a brilliant listener said suchet 
agatha christie was very clever with arthur hastings she didnt 
make him a dimwit she gave him a sidekick who can reason with him 
as a reader would hastings goes for the obvious that allows 
poirot to take his ideas off the wall he doesnt believe what he 
sees 
its a clever device that allows poirot to do all this 
thinking and then flash his green light and arrive at the 
solution 
the eccentric little detective first appeared in the 1920 book 
the mysterious affair at styles 
agatha christie had no idea he would become so popular 
suchet said she once said had she known she would have made him 
younger he must have been 180 when he died in the last book the 
final curtain she wrote something like 40 short stories and 30 
books 
