<TEXT>
you just received that longawaited job 
promotion on the west coast but you cannot move the family into a 
new home until your condominium in the northeast is sold 
or youve discovered your dream house could be had for a song 
but only if you raise the money from the sale of your present home 
before another anxious buyer gets there 
in both situations the bottlenecked homeowner could use a quick 
cash fix to bridge the gap between the purchase of the new home and 
sale of the old 
bridge or swing loans offer consumers the shortterm 
financing usually three to six months to cover the new down 
payment and closing costs these loans have been around a number of 
years helping buyers take quick advantage of a home bargain make 
a down payment on a house under construction or simply relieve some 
of the presssure of househunting 
but experts warn theyre not for everyone particularly those 
likely to need them most these days homesellers living in regions 
where sales have been especially soft 
what you have to emphasize is that theres a buyer beware 
warning on this product said tara little a spokeswoman for the 
american bankers association a washingtonbased trade group if 
things fall through and the borrower cant find a buyer for the 
first home he still has to pay off the loan 
an alternative may be to get a longerterm standard homeequity 
loan to cover the down payment on a new home and rent the old house 
until its sold the interest on both types of loans is fully 
deductible up to 100000 however one disadvantage to home equity 
loans is they take much longer to process 
bridge loans though arent easy to obtain while there are few 
available statistics some experts estimate only about a quarter to 
a third of all banks and thrifts nationwide regularly offer them 
those that do rarely promote them in 14 years of publishing 
i doubt weve seen more than two bridge loan ads said robert 
heady who runs the north palm beach fla publication bank rate 
monitor 
further complicating matters is that most lenders negotiate 
bridge loans on a casebycase basis with terms depending largely 
on an individuals credit history 
lenders say they look for borrowers with steady income little 
creditcard debt or major loans besides a mortgage and with a home 
in a fairly stable housing market 
if its in a good market well do it in a depressed 
marketplace well back away said michael g noah director of 
consumer lending for goldome bank in buffalo ny the last thing 
we want to do is get into the real estate market 
noah said goldomes loans are secured by the equity in the 
property up for sale 
to provide a safety cushion most lenders offer bridge loans 
equal to around 75 percent to 80 percent of the value of the 
borrowers current home minus outstanding mortgages provided the 
home is under contract to a buyer some banks will lend a little 
less without a contract 
say john and mary homeowner need money in a hurry for a 
downpayment on a 300000 home the house they have is valued at 
250000 and they have 90000 left on their primary mortgage 
based on the 75 percent safety cushion they technically could 
be eligible to borrow up to 97500 or almost a third of the value 
of the new house 
many lenders will only make these loans to first mortgage 
applicants said paul havemann a vice president at butler 
njbased hsh associates which publishes mortgage market 
information 
some insist on interest payments only on a monthly basis with 
the balance to be repaid when the loan is due others ask for no 
payment until the note is due havemann said 
the interest on bridge loans is linked to the prime rate plus 
one or two percentage points some lenders charge more in addition 
to tacking on hefty loan origination fees 
a fortunate few homeowners however can get help from their 
employer 
many of the nations biggest companies provide relocating 
workers with interestfree bridge loans said charles martel 
director of client relations for phh homequity the wilton conn 
company buys the homes of employees on behalf of client companies 
employees based on the homes appraised value and resells them 
martel said hes seen about a 10 percent jump nationwide in 
companysponsored bridge loans over last year he said hes also 
seen a rise in the number of employees who opt for phh homequity to 
buy their home rather than sell it themselves 55 percent this 
year vs around 40 percent a year ago 
