institutions lend money to farmers and the fmha provides a 
guarantee that the debt will be repaid however guarantees have 
not been popular with many hardpressed farmers because of higher 
interest rates charged by commercial lenders 
wherever possible new borrowers will be assisted through 
guaranteed rather than direct loans and existing borrowers will be 
graduated to private sector credit using a guarantee where 
necessary said the usda analysis this shift will allow fmha 
