i remember the 35th anniversary in 1984 he says i was in 
the square it seemed the communist party was at its highest level 
of prestige every sector of society peasants workers students 
all had so much hope in the reforms that senior leader deng 
xiaoping was enacting to shake up the economy 
i wish that time could return 
he still pays his monthly party dues of 24 cents and still 
believes deng is one of the greatest figures in chinese history 
despite his orders to crush the spring movement 
it was deng who opened our eyes who opened china and let 
foreigners come in and chinese go out this cannot be wiped out 
he says as for whether the party can save china we will have to 
see right now there is no organization that can substitute for it 
i think i am a good party member the partys guiding 
principles say the party works for the interests of the vast 
majority i think what i did in tiananmen square was for the vast 
majority 
ordinary criminals freed from jail often are given their old 
jobs back to aid their rehabilitation but gao says that when he 
went back to beijing normal university the school refused to let 
him resume work 
it did not formally fire him either meaning that in chinas 
controlled job market he is not free to seek new work so he is 
taking turns living with friends hou zhang and others 
they told me to wait so im waiting he says 
meanwhile gao says he can no longer think of marrying zhang 
