quaker oats co says it funds oatbran research 
to learn more about oats not to produce studies that will help 
sell its products 
i think its safe to say that if quaker had not been providing 
research funding to universities for the past 25 years the amount 
of information known about oats in general would be far less than 
it is said ron bottrell a spokesman for the chicagobased 
company 
bottrells comments tuesday came after the company disclosed it 
is funding research aimed at substantiating the health benefits of 
oat bran 
quakers researchsupported claim that oatbran can help lower 
cholesterol was challenged recently by a harvard medical study of 
the heavily marketed food product 
bottrell declined to describe two oatbran studies partially 
funded by quaker that he said have been under way for more than a 
year but he said quaker also helped fund a syracuse university 
study announced last week that supported findings that a lowfat 
diet supplemented with oat bran can help lower cholesterol in the 
bloodstream 
bottrell said he saw no conflict in quaker which controls about 
70 percent of the oatbran market financing research that 
theoretically could help sales of its products 
were not saying the new studies will be a direct refutation 
of the medical study but we think it will add to information about 
the benefits of oats and oat bran bottrell said 
the harvard study published in the jan 19 issue of the new 
england journal of medicine disputed findings that oat bran can 
help lower cholesterol when eaten daily as part of a lowfat 
lowcholesterol diet 
the syracuse study which will be published in the february 
issue of the journal of the american dietetic association agreed 
with the harvard finding that people who add oat bran to their diet 
tend to cut down on other foods thereby reducing their total fat 
intake 
but the syracuse researchers did not conclude as the harvard 
study did that oat bran alone has no special cholesterolreducing 
properties 
quaker has responded to the harvard study with newspaper ads 
citing 10 other studies conducted over the past 27 years that 
indicated oat bran has special cholesterollowering properties 
bottrell said five of those studies were partially funded by 
quaker with additional funding from health or government agencies 
we are in the oats business and we consider it our business 
anything pertaining to oats bottrell said in a telephone 
interview 
meanwhile an informal national survey of about a dozen grocery 
chains by grocery marketing magazine showed no drop in sales of 
oatbran cereals since the harvard study was published said ryan 
mathews the detroitbased editor of the magazine which is 
published in chicago 
our feeling is that the oatbran products most at risk are the 
peripheral products that have come on the market in the last couple 
of years mathews said in a telephone interview 
peripheral products he said include oatbran snack chips 
pretzels and beer which are among the hundreds of oatbran 
products introduced in the past two years 
mathews story on the survey will be published in the february 
issue of grocery marketing 
