economic forecasts are a major factor in preparation of a 
federal budget for example if the inflation rate is higher than 
forecast the deficit could be worsened considerably because many 
federal programs including social security are increased 
automatically with the inflation rate 
the 1991 budget of 123 trillion is based on an omb forecast 
