rigging the world series 
missouri was the 40th jurisdiction with which drexel has 
settled the new yorkbased firm said it has paid a total of 73 
million so far in settlements 
drexel pleaded guilty last september to six felonies and paid 
650 million to settle a range of fraud allegations stemming from 
the governments lengthy investigation of insider trading on wall 
street 
drexel also agreed to dozens of administrative changes and 
unprecedented federal supervision in the april settlement of civil 
charges by the federal securities and exchange commission 
under the latest agreement drexel cannot solicit new business 
in missouri for three years without the secretary of states 
consent must hire an agent to find investors hurt by the companys 
actions and must pay 100000 above the 1 million to a national 
investor education fund 
the company can continue to deal with its existing customers in 
missouri 
of drexels payments to the state 500000 pay for toward 
investor education materials and an equal amount for grants for 
business programs at missouri colleges and universities 
blunt said persons found to have been financially hurt by 
drexels action are entitled to money from a 350 million fund 
under a settlement between the firm and the government investors 
who file a claim must prove damage 
settling with the states relieves the firm of possible 
litigation and frees state regulators from having to investigate 
the firms trading activities from 1984 to 1986 when the sec 
alleged the fraud occurred 
it also generally preserves the firms ability to underwrite 
securities and do other business in the states most states can 
revoke a companys right to do business if the firm is convicted 
or admits to committing a felony drexel abandoned the retail 
brokerage business last year 
