orion pictures corp was wrongly identified 
as a creditor of film maker francis ford coppolas zoetrope 
productions in a bankruptcy filing made last week zoetrope said 
wednesday 
the filing for protection under chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy 
law said zoetrope owed orion 62 million 
orion issued a statement wednesday saying it was not owed the 
money asked about that san franciscobased zoetrope referred 
calls to an outside publicist ginger slaughter who gave the 
following statement 
zoetrope productions believes that the debt listed in its 
chapter 11 filing as due orion is not in fact due orion 
ms slaughter said she did not know who the real creditor is 
the biggest creditors accounting for more than half the total 
zoetrope debt are production companies coppola set up to film the 
movies the outsiders and rumble fish in the early 1980s 
they are owed 162 million according to the filing 
