<DOCNO> AP900131-0305 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
federal regulators on wednesday seized 
phoenixbased merabank arizonas largest savings institution and 
the latest victim of the states real estate slump 
the resolution trust corp took over merabank after the office 
of thrift supervision declared that the thrift was operating in an 
unsafe and unsound condition 
the action comes despite a dec 7 pledge by the thrifts parent 
company pinnacle west capital corp to inject 450 million by 
march 31 into its troubled subsidiary in exchange for a release 
from further obligation 
the thrift office said it still expected pinnacle west which 
owns arizonas largest utility arizona public service co to 
comply with the agreement however it said the infusion would 
still leave merabank far short of its capital requirement and said 
the thrift continued to weaken 
henry b sargent jr pinnacle wests chief financial officer 
said the holding company would honor the agreement 
this receivership doesnt affect our agreement with the ots at 
all we didnt know when this was going to happen but it was not 
an unexpected event sargent added 
wednesday also was the deadline for pinnacle west to domplete a 
624 debt million restructuring required by regulators to make sure 
the holding company would be able to handle another 450 million in 
debt 
all 45 lenders involved had to sign the restructuring document 
and sargent said late in the evening that only one signature had 
not been obtained he said the company was not working for other 
standstill agreements after five extensions of the original 
jan 7 deadline 
at the end of november merabank was 337 million in the red 
with 66 billion in assets it is arizonas largest sampl it was 
ranked 29th nationwide at midyear by sheshunoff information 
services inc an austin texas consulting firm 
regulators said all merabank branches will remain open for 
business as usual operating under a new governmentowned thrift 
called merabank federal savings bank deposits will be insured up 
to 100000 per account 
merabank is the sixth arizona savings and loan to be seized by 
the government leaving only four operating privately the states 
secondlargest western savings and loan association of phoenix 
was seized in june and put up for sale earlier this month 
arizona has been hard hit by a real estate slump home prices in 
phoenix for instance fell 61 percent between the third quarter 
of 1989 and the same period a year earlier according to the 
national association of realtors 
merabank operates a subsidiary in el paso texas merabank 
texas which was a buyer in the 1988 governmentassisted bailout of 
three texas sampls it got about 670 million from the government to 
acquire state federal lubbock first financial el paso and 
brownfield federal brownfield 
the texas thrifts along with merabanks other holdings in the 
state now fall back into the governments possession 
merabank is the 32nd sampl failure so far this year an additional 
225 to 295 are likely to fail compared with a record 328 last year 
and 223 in 1988 
merabank was purchased for 426 million by pinnacle west in 
december 1986 the same year the states real estate market hit the 
skids the sampl has been suffering for some time losing 209 
million in 1988 and more than 190 million through the first three 
quarters of 1989 
the thrift had about 45 billion in deposits in 833000 
accounts 
</TEXT>
